name: Dylan Woessner
text: A good space for getting a sense of the towns history. There are three rooms containing artifacts and photographs from the town, it's people, and their contributions. The lady working there when we visited was very nice and helpful and answered all our questions reliably. Plus the building itself is quite beautiful and worth the stop to see even if you don't go inside.

name: John Hartman
text: A wonderful museum full of local history and information. Not sure if the trash panda outside is a pet but he sure was friendly! Highly recommend this place. It's free entry but please leave a large donation so they can keep it going!

name: Michael Ramer
text: Very nice museum! Great to visit to see the history of Fort Payne. Staff was very knowledgeable about the city's history.

name: Maxwell Walden
text: Couldn't go in today due to COVID-19 so we looked at it with Christmas decorations on display outside.

name: samuel rowell
text: The place is a good place to learn local history it also has a nice staff

name: Margaret Webb
text: Been trying for 2 years to go here. Finally and it was worth the wait.    Loved it and really loved the annex. Fort Payne citizens sure have done a lot to protect their history.... Would recommend this to everyone...

name: I.E. Xam
text: Very nicely preserved. Rare depot made of stone in the South.

name: Rebecca Gass
text: 1st time. Really enjoyed my visit!!! So glad that this piece of our history has been preserved. Plan on returning.

name: Kimberly
text: Intresting things to learn from here

name: Susanna Maroon
text: Beautiful place to take any kind of picture
